nson became headmaster of the Thacher School in 1936, twelve years after his father Sherman's 1931 death and after a five-year interregnum under Morgan Barnes. He led the school for thirteen years and was the last member of the Thacher family ever to head the school; under him the student body expanded from Sherman's ~60-boy cap to 94 boys."},{"number":3,"category":"civic","header":"Civic leader of Ojai across four institutions","body":"In addition to teaching, Anson served as president of the Ojai Civic Association, Ojai Chamber of Commerce, the Senior Canyon Mutual Water Co. (30+ years), and the Ojai Valley School District Board of Trustees. He and his wife Margaret were honored as grand marshals of Ojai's 1989 Independence Day parade."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"anson-thacher-1905"},"HD4118":{"id":"HD4118","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Anne","middle_name":"T.","last_name":"Adami","maiden_name":"Thacher","married_names":["Adami"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Anne T. Thacher Adami"},"birth":{},"baptism":{},"death":{},"residence":{"city":"Walnut Creek","county":"Contra Costa County","state":"California","country":"United States"},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":11,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD4102","father_name":"Anson Stiles Thacher","mother_id":"I00597","mother_name":"Margaret Robertson Pascoe Thacher"},"marriages":[],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[],